definitions.definition: Water, especially in a river or other body of water , that has a naturally dark appearance.

subdefinitions.definition: Water that contains dark organic matter such as loam or tannins .
Water that is acidic and low in nutrients.

definitions.definition: Blackwater fever ; malaria caused by Plasmodium falciparum .
Waste from domestic toilets; water containing fecal matter.

main_definition: Water, especially in a river or other body of water , that has a naturally dark appearance.
secondary_definitions: Blackwater fever ; malaria caused by Plasmodium falciparum . [from 19th c.]
Waste from domestic toilets; water containing fecal matter. [from 20th c.]
